article.headline: UNC Greensboro defeats Chowan 97-58
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- Kyle Cain scored a game-high 17 points, joining four teammates in double figures, to lead UNC Greensboro to a 97-58 victory over D-II Chowan on Sunday. Cain scored seven points in the opening five minutes, helping to propel UNC Greensboro (2-1) to a 13-7 lead. The Spartans were ahead 49-25 at halftime. RJ White made 11 rebounds as UNC Greensboro owned a 50-22 advantage on the boards. Tevon Saddler, who had led the team in its previous two games, added 15 points, Tyrone Outlaw 13, Clay Byrd 12 and Kayel Locke 11 for the Spartans. Warren Powers led Chowan (0-2) with 15 points. The Hawks shot only 36 percent from the field and took only 11 free throws, making eight. UNC Greensboro hit 57 percent of its field goals and sank 18 of 31 from the free throw line.
